The paper deals with the complexity of deciding correctness for proof nets in pomset logic, which is a topic in logic and theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses graph-theoretic techniques, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with formal languages and automata, which could place it under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The complexity analysis of the problem could also make it relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and the use of graph theory could make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
